The husband of Fausta was Annius Milo, and the Scholiast Acron says that Villius is put for Annius, as Mal- thinus for Maecenas (see above, v. 25), Licinia for Terentia (see C. ii. 12, Iun-o· duction). But, as Bentley rightly ob- serves, Horace is not speaking of husbands here.
